rules.natural: Either there is public support, or if an organization requests funding, then a government approves funding.
Provided that a region has an active hurricane, flooding occurs in that region.
A region has an active hurricane or an organization engages in international coordination.
Whenever flooding occurs in a region, evacuation is ordered for that region.
Under the condition that the media issues conflicting reports, it is not the case that evacuation is ordered for a region.
Either a region experiences severe damage or a region suffers infrastructure collapse.

If a region suffers infrastructure collapse, then provided that the absence of international coordination by an organization implies that the organization requests aid for the region, the organization deploys aid to the region.

If a region has mass casualties, then provided that the absence of international coordination by an organization implies that the organization requests aid for the region, the organization deploys aid to the region.
Whenever an organization completes its assessment, then if the region experiences severe damage, the region has mass casualties.
If an organization has food available, then that organization conducts ration distribution.
An organization has food available or an organization has logistics ready.
If it is not the case that having logistics ready implies international coordination by an organization, then the organization requests funding.
If it is not the case that having logistics ready implies international coordination by an organization, then it is not the case that a government approves funding.
If the absence of international coordination by an organization implies that the organization requests aid for a region, then it is not the case that the organization deploys aid to the region.
If an organization does not engage in international coordination, then it is not the case that the organization requests aid for a region.
